00:49:17.210 --> 00:49:19.320
So there's obviously
an element here

00:49:19.320 --> 00:49:23.050
of us figuring out a
mathematical language

00:49:23.050 --> 00:49:25.740
to do the tasks that we
are interested in doing,

00:49:25.740 --> 00:49:28.385
guided by the physical world.

00:49:28.385 --> 00:49:31.260
It's very important
though to distinguish

00:49:31.260 --> 00:49:34.490
between the language of
mathematics, which we invent,

00:49:34.490 --> 00:49:37.620
like the notation for how
we write the number 5,

00:49:37.620 --> 00:49:39.800
and the structures
of mathematics,

00:49:39.800 --> 00:49:41.410
which are the things
that I'm claiming

00:49:41.410 --> 00:49:43.180
exist independently of people.

00:49:43.180 --> 00:49:46.071
So to clarify this a little bit,
think of Plato, for example.

00:49:46.071 --> 00:49:48.070
He was really interested
in this simple question

00:49:48.070 --> 00:49:51.950
of how many regular
three dimensional shapes

00:49:51.950 --> 00:49:57.530
there were that you can make
just out of identical polygons.

00:49:57.530 --> 00:50:00.320
And he figured out that
there are five of them,

00:50:00.320 --> 00:50:02.220
which we call Platonic solids.

00:50:02.220 --> 00:50:05.820
Now, he was free to invent the
language for describing them,

00:50:05.820 --> 00:50:09.180
to call them the tetrahedron,
the cube, the octahedron,

00:50:09.180 --> 00:50:11.610
the dodecahedron,
and the icosahedron.

00:50:11.610 --> 00:50:15.090
He could have called the last
one shmicosehedron or something

00:50:15.090 --> 00:50:16.220
else, right?

00:50:16.220 --> 00:50:19.660
But he was not free
to invent a sixth one.

00:50:19.660 --> 00:50:23.490
That's the aspect that
just exists mathematically,

00:50:23.490 --> 00:50:26.480
that we are not free to invent
the structures themselves,

00:50:26.480 --> 00:50:29.280
that there is such a thing as
a dodecahedron that has exactly

00:50:29.280 --> 00:50:33.120
four cousins--
not five, not two.

00:50:33.120 --> 00:50:34.780
That's the thing
which is out there.

00:50:34.780 --> 00:50:36.390
So the way I envision
this is we have

00:50:36.390 --> 00:50:38.240
all these mathematical
structures,

00:50:38.240 --> 00:50:44.280
the Platonic solids, the
integers, Hilbert space, the 3

00:50:44.280 --> 00:50:46.910
plus 1 dimensional,
pseudo-Riemannian manifolds--

00:50:46.910 --> 00:50:47.910
put in your favorite.

00:50:47.910 --> 00:50:51.410
There's an infinite set of
these mathematical structures

00:50:51.410 --> 00:50:52.110
out there.

00:50:52.110 --> 00:50:55.220
Some of them we find
useful to study,

00:50:55.220 --> 00:50:57.470
because they help with
finance, or building bridges,

00:50:57.470 --> 00:50:57.840
or whatever.

00:50:57.840 --> 00:50:59.548
And we give them names,
and we teach them

00:50:59.548 --> 00:51:00.720
to our children at school.

00:51:00.720 --> 00:51:03.570
Others, we haven't even
discovered them yet,

00:51:03.570 --> 00:51:05.800
because they weren't
relevant before us.

00:51:05.800 --> 00:51:11.890
But the set of them
that's out there

00:51:11.890 --> 00:51:13.660
has nothing to do with us.

00:51:13.660 --> 00:51:15.660
It's not because of
our doing that there

00:51:15.660 --> 00:51:17.240
are five platonic solids.

00:51:17.240 --> 00:51:20.300
So I think of it as
much like if someone

00:51:20.300 --> 00:51:21.760
comes to Boston
for the first time,

00:51:21.760 --> 00:51:25.237
they've never been here, which
exact streets they choose

00:51:25.237 --> 00:51:27.320
to explore will depend a
lot on their preferences,

00:51:27.320 --> 00:51:30.090
like where they work, what
food they like to eat.

00:51:30.090 --> 00:51:34.200
But then if no one tells them
what these things are called,

00:51:34.200 --> 00:51:36.470
they might even invent
their own language for it.

00:51:36.470 --> 00:51:40.070
We're exploring this
mathematical space,

00:51:40.070 --> 00:51:42.576
to first explore the things
that are useful for us.

00:51:42.576 --> 00:51:44.200
If you have an alien
civilization which

00:51:44.200 --> 00:51:46.070
start to study math,
they would probably

00:51:46.070 --> 00:51:48.390
start exploring a lot
of other structures

00:51:48.390 --> 00:51:51.340
that we haven't bothered
with, and maybe vice versa.

00:51:51.340 --> 00:51:53.510
But I also suspect that
there are some things which

00:51:53.510 --> 00:51:56.360
are so central in math that
pretty much any aliens that

00:51:56.360 --> 00:51:58.090
want to do any kind
of serious technology

00:51:58.090 --> 00:52:01.780
would find it useful to,
again, discover the integers,

00:52:01.780 --> 00:52:08.280
for example, and doing Boolean
logic with zero and ones,

00:52:08.280 --> 00:52:09.740
and maybe they
would make computers

00:52:09.740 --> 00:52:12.240
that had logic much
like ours, and so on.

00:52:12.240 --> 00:52:13.764
Because it's just
like anyone who

00:52:13.764 --> 00:52:15.430
spends enough time
in Boston is at least

00:52:15.430 --> 00:52:20.180
going to discover Boston
Common and downtown.

00:52:20.180 --> 00:52:20.907
Question?

00:52:20.907 --> 00:52:21.490
AUDIENCE: Yes.

00:52:21.490 --> 00:52:25.720
So intuitively, I
agree with and I

00:52:25.720 --> 00:52:29.390
believe what you claim about
that it is just math all

00:52:29.390 --> 00:52:31.550
the way down, that it's
not just the description

00:52:31.550 --> 00:52:34.240
of some underlying
