00:52:52.572 --> 00:52:54.530
Because it's about the
relationships of things.

00:52:54.530 --> 00:52:55.613
MAX TEGMARK: That's right.

00:52:55.613 --> 00:52:57.570
AUDIENCE: Math is
fundamentally about that.

00:52:57.570 --> 00:53:00.860
It's uninteresting or not
being applied if you're just

00:53:00.860 --> 00:53:04.240
talking about expressions not
in the context of an equality,

00:53:04.240 --> 00:53:06.360
or an equation, or a
comparison to something else.

00:53:06.360 --> 00:53:07.405
So it's all about relations.

00:53:07.405 --> 00:53:08.200
MAX TEGMARK: That's right.

00:53:08.200 --> 00:53:09.410
It is all about relations.

00:53:09.410 --> 00:53:10.200
I agree.

00:53:10.200 --> 00:53:11.191
AUDIENCE: And the
fact that we know

00:53:11.191 --> 00:53:13.280
there's not some underlying
reality that we can never

00:53:13.280 --> 00:53:14.863
directly perceive,
because we can only

00:53:14.863 --> 00:53:16.950
see the indirect relationships
and the transitive

00:53:16.950 --> 00:53:18.970
relationships that we can
measure these numbers about.

00:53:18.970 --> 00:53:19.720
MAX TEGMARK: Yeah.

00:53:19.720 --> 00:53:21.640
You're making a very
good set of points there.

00:53:21.640 --> 00:53:24.640
Let me just add a little bit
how I think to them, as well.

00:53:24.640 --> 00:53:27.260
First of all, in
mathematics, the way

00:53:27.260 --> 00:53:29.280
a mathematical
structure is defined

00:53:29.280 --> 00:53:33.490
is simply as an abstract set
of elements and relations

00:53:33.490 --> 00:53:35.180
between them.

00:53:35.180 --> 00:53:38.050
You can give names to
these abstract elements

00:53:38.050 --> 00:53:40.839
and call them the edges of
your dodecahedron, or whatever.

00:53:40.839 --> 00:53:41.880
But that's not necessary.

00:53:44.550 --> 00:53:46.800
The elements of a
set in mathematics

00:53:46.800 --> 00:53:48.640
don't have any
properties at all.

00:53:48.640 --> 00:53:52.260
And when physics began, when
Archimedes, and Galileo,

00:53:52.260 --> 00:53:55.360
and others were doing
their stuff, at that point,

00:53:55.360 --> 00:53:57.360
the relations they
discovered with equations

00:53:57.360 --> 00:54:01.280
could only capture
a very small subset

00:54:01.280 --> 00:54:04.070
of all the properties of
nature, mostly motion of things.

00:54:04.070 --> 00:54:07.140
So Galileo was very good at
figuring how this would move.

00:54:07.140 --> 00:54:09.640
But he had no idea where
the atoms came from

00:54:09.640 --> 00:54:12.030
or why this was black
and why this was hard,

00:54:12.030 --> 00:54:15.510
even though his skin
was soft, and so on.

00:54:15.510 --> 00:54:18.280
So it seemed like you had
these mathematical relations

00:54:18.280 --> 00:54:21.280
between things which were
very non-mathematical

00:54:21.280 --> 00:54:22.280
in their properties.

00:54:22.280 --> 00:54:23.926
Gradually, that changed.

00:54:23.926 --> 00:54:25.300
Then we got the
Maxwell equations

00:54:25.300 --> 00:54:27.427
which explains, actually,
what colors are.

00:54:27.427 --> 00:54:30.010
And then we got the Schrodinger
equation of quantum mechanics,

00:54:30.010 --> 00:54:32.490
which actually lets me
calculate why this is black,

00:54:32.490 --> 00:54:34.840
and why my shirt looks
blue, and why this is soft,

00:54:34.840 --> 00:54:38.260
and why this is hard, and all
the other properties of matter.

00:54:38.260 --> 00:54:41.029
And now, we instead
have realized

00:54:41.029 --> 00:54:43.320
that we can understand all
this with quantum mechanics,

00:54:43.320 --> 00:54:45.070
and looking at these
smaller building

00:54:45.070 --> 00:54:46.450
blocks, quarks and electrons.

00:54:46.450 --> 00:54:50.860
And as I said earlier, a quark
isn't actually soft, or hard,

00:54:50.860 --> 00:54:52.200
or yellow, or blue.

00:54:52.200 --> 00:54:53.910
It doesn't have any
of those properties.

00:54:53.910 --> 00:54:55.490
In fact, we've
looked really hard

00:54:55.490 --> 00:54:57.240
and haven't discovered
any property yet

00:54:57.240 --> 00:55:02.610
that a quark or an electron has
other than just some numbers.

00:55:02.610 --> 00:55:06.031
So that's why our
world is feeling more

00:55:06.031 --> 00:55:07.280
like a mathematical structure.

00:55:07.280 --> 00:55:08.821
The relations are
there, and we found

00:55:08.821 --> 00:55:10.050
more and more relationships.

00:55:10.050 --> 00:55:12.140
We know more relationships
now than ever before.

00:55:12.140 --> 00:55:14.390
But the things that the
relationships or relationships

00:55:14.390 --> 00:55:17.570
between have lost
much of their magic.

00:55:17.570 --> 00:55:19.620
And as far as we can
tell, actually, they

00:55:19.620 --> 00:55:21.910
don't have any properties
at all except numbers.

00:55:21.910 --> 00:55:24.800
But this ain't over yet.

00:55:24.800 --> 00:55:26.840
There are still
things in the world

00:55:26.840 --> 00:55:29.907
that we have epically failed
to describe with math,

00:55:29.907 --> 00:55:31.740
so we should be humble
and acknowledge that.

00:55:31.740 --> 00:55:33.415
For example, our consciousness.

00:55:36.195 --> 00:55:38.320
Some people think we'll
never be able to understand

00:55:38.320 --> 00:55:41.430
our consciousness with
mathematics and equations.

00:55:41.430 --> 00:55:42.680
Other people think we do.

00:55:42.680 --> 00:55:45.375
For example, Giulio
Tononi and Christof Koch,

00:55:45.375 --> 00:55:47.510
two famous neuroscientists,
have this theory

00:55:47.510 --> 00:55:52.470
where they argue that
conscious is actually

00:55:52.470 --> 00:55:55.327
certain mathematical pattern to
do with information processing.

00:55:55.327 --> 00:55:57.160
And we don't know yet
what's right or wrong.

00:55:57.160 --> 00:55:59.700
And I think one of
the coolest things

00:55:59.700 --> 00:56:01.530
to watch to see which
way this is going

00:56:01.530 --> 00:56:04.110
to break is to see
whether ultimately

00:56:04.110 --> 00:56:06.760
even that aspect of nature is
something we can understand

00:56:06.760 --> 00:56:08.390
better with science,
or whether we're

00:56:08.390 --> 00:56:10.730
going to hit the
road block there.

00:56:10.730 --> 00:56:13.849
Do we have time for
one more question?

